		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=2457">North Freeport</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Zimel's Blades</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Zimel's Blades</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=367476"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:jwmaaske@students.wisc.edu">Palasees</a> | 
		                        2/19/2001 1:50:40 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">I'm stuck on a quest for Pallys.  I talked to the lady paladin on the arch above the entrance to the halls of truth (I forget her name) and she told me to take a note to a spy in the freeport militia.  I did this and the militia guy got killed by the guards there, but he gave me a scrap that said something about Zimel's blades on it and he told me to give it to that same lady on the arch above the halls of truth sign.  She wonders about &quot;Zimel's blades&quot; for a while and sends me off to the Freeport office of the people to talk to the woman in the room upstairs (sorry I forget her name too) about [Zimel's blades].<BR>
<BR>
She says this was an old weapons shop in the East Freeport zone, and that she had to shut it down a number of years ago.  She said that Groflah Steadirt (spelling?) at Groflah's weapon shop near the bard guild in North Freeport used to be a good friend of [Ariska Zimel] who used to run Zimel's blades.  You can ask her about Groflah and she'll say that Groflah and Ariska used to go way back, and they learned how to smith together.  She also clues that Groflah's weapon shop got some loot from Zimel's blades when it went under, but it was mostly charred junk.  Also she says that the building is currently for rent in EFP's slums.<BR>
<BR>
Here's where I get stuck.  She tells me to ask Groflah about Ariska Zimel, and when I do, Groflah denies knowing about Zimel and tells me to get out of the store.  (hehe if I hail him again he's bright and cheery and wants me to buy stuff)  Anyways, how do I complete this quest?  I've gone to the place that's for rent in EFP slums, but there's nothing there (except for the rogue, necro, and SK guilds where pallys get killed A LOT).  The woman on the arch doesn't respond to anything about Groflah or Ariska or charred junk for that matter.   <BR>
<BR>
HELP!<BR>
<BR>
Palasees<BR>
15th Paladin, no guild<BR>
Bertoxxulus server
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
