			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok when you hail Groflah he tells you his is too busy for anything but selling, if you hand him the item list he will then open up a bit about zimels blades..he will say to meet him near seafares roost by the docks at night. I have never seen him there at night. It is suposed to be sometime between 5 and 6 am. Well here is the spoiler..you dont really need to see him to complete this quest as long as you have all he info. Heres what you do..go into Seafares..wait for a guy named Tykar Renlin. He looks like a beggar. Give him 4 Drom Champagnes (can be bought at searfares) give him one at a time. Dont take your time with this either or he will despawn. Thus losing the droms that you gave him and then you will have to wait around again for him to spawn. Upon giving him all 4 droms you will get a blanket and xp. He tells you to take the blanket to a friend that is a prisoner in the arena. Ok besides the blanket you need edible goo and bog juice. You can make the edible goo easy if you dont have cooking skill even (get 1 ratear, and a fire beetle eye) Take them to a stove put both ear and eye in and combine..thus one edible goo. Now off to the arena you go.. go around the ramp of the arena til you see a barred gate..go downstairs and you will see several cells..the prisoner is in the first one (this is Zimel by the way) Ok hail him and he says something incoherant. Give him the blanket then he will say bog and goo. Give him the bog juice first then the edible goo. You will recieve a key and xp. Ok now you need to go to Highhold keep. In HH keep there is a banker you must see..you cant hail her so be careful about not giving to the wrong banker..she will be the first one you see going in. Give her the key and she gives you a letter and a little xp. She says sorry to see you check out here is your mail. Now you need to take the letter to Brother Hayle in South Karana (he looks like a splitpaw gnoll) He is a good guy though. Give him the letter and he will tell you everything you need to complete the rest of the quest.. what items you need and from whom. Ok well that is as far as I have gotten. You know I have one complaint about this quest..without some spoiler messages for this quest it could never be completed. Well I hope this helps a bit for you all. Take care and happy hunting.<BR>
<BR>
 
